</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udeeveeusshaddowblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deeveeus Shaddowblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/3/02 5:31:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12268.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/Deeveeus%20Shaddowblade/fullsize/Elf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pickpocketing Tani?</span><hr size=1> I've only just posted a plan in the Training studio - i got both notes without agro once, my skill is at 200. I'm a half-elf tunare follower so after killing guards at lower levels while pk'ing i am uber kos even in DE form guards hate me =p. anyway here it is - let me know what you think.<br>
<br>
Obtaining the second part of the note from Tani in Neriak 3rd Gate for the epic can be done by sneaking in and picking it from his pocket – no sweat right? Not on a PvP server it’s not, not when you’re a Half-Elf sneaking into Darkie controlled territory. So what do you do? Nervous about trying it? I DO know friends who have sneaked in and got past the Darkies and picked him until he agro’d then tried to run to zone through the Guards and were killed, another friend camped by him and picked when he could until he got it. Yet another friend managed to get a bind inside Neriak zone line and died 2 exp deaths and 10 PvP deaths before he got it, he was lucky he managed to get a bind! Me? Did it another way, and I liked it so much I thought I’d share it with you. My trusty Cleric friend Belshazar heard me mention in Guild-chat that I was about to go in and get the note. He came to WC and suggested a crafty little plan which I immediately liked.<br>
<br>
I promptly jumped in the water in WC and drowned myself, then immediately consented Belshazar. He dragged my corpse out of the water (having had the pleasure of watching me drown) and revived me. First part done. I took my Jboots from my corpse (not necessary if ya can get a SoW) and a Shiny Brass Idol (casts a 12 second invulnerability, drops from named Orc in HPH by the Kith zoneline, somewhat rare drop I believe).<br>
<br>
Now the second part of the plan, cunningly simple. Run up to Nektulos and get over on the right-hand (east) wall, hide/sneak all the way up to Neriak and in you go, immediately hitting hide/sneak when you get in. Make your way over to Neriak Commons and again zone and hit Hide/Sneak as soon as you get in. Make you way down to Neriak 3rd Gate and zone in, again hitting Hide/Sneak. No NPC sees invis on the way down, not even the PoD (whom I wasn’t sure of). Sneak in to the Rogue Guild and Tani N’Mar is there on the platform. Now a little preparation, I switched the Shiny Brass Idol with my Jboots hotkey and positioned myself behind Tani. The idea here is that you Pickpocket, Pickpocket, Pickpocket until you get the note (if you’re lucky enough that he has spawned with it), then activate the Idol if he agro’s and call for a Revive. With luck, your Revive will arrive before your Invulnerability runs out and that’s it, you’re out with the note!<br>
<br>
As it turns out, I was hidden/sneaking behind Tani and picked him – 4 gold. Picked him again – got the note! No agro, called for revive and I was out!<br>
<br>
Quite an exciting little thing to do all the same and I got a buzz from the adrenaline. Lucky no PC’s had See-Invis up or if they did they did not register my presence, not even a stop and look, maybe because I looked like I was on a CR.<br>
<br>
Thought this might help out some Rogue on his way to obtaining his note, I certainly liked the plan! Thanks to Belshazar =)<br>
<br>
Deeveeus<br>
Vallon<br>
